cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with network-adaptive error control for low-latency interactive streaming, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the construction of practical low-latency streaming codes, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
